# Vite only exposes variables prefixed with VITE_

# ── Supabase (auth + catalog) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Project Settings → API. Anon key is intended for browser use (RLS still applies).
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# ── Option A: Inline list (no manifest, no bucket listing) ────────────────────
# VITE_VIDEO_SOURCES=https://storage.googleapis.com/BUCKET/a.mp4,b.mp4

# ── Option B: manifest.json in the bucket ────────────────────────────────────
# VITE_GCS_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://storage.googleapis.com/videos-bucket-123
# VITE_VIDEO_MANIFEST_PATH=manifest.json
# If manifest.json is missing (404), the app tries XML bucket listing when the
# base URL is https://storage.googleapis.com/BUCKET (same as Option C).

# ── Option C: “API-style” listing from the browser (XML List Bucket) ──────────
# This is NOT your Console session — it is an anonymous HTTP list to GCS.
# Requires IAM that allows public listing (e.g. allUsers: Storage Object Viewer
# on the bucket). Same CORS concerns as fetching a JSON manifest.
# VITE_GCS_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://storage.googleapis.com/videos-bucket-123
# VITE_GCS_USE_XML_LIST=true
# Optional: only keys under this prefix (folder in the bucket)
# VITE_GCS_LIST_PREFIX=uploads/

# If you use Option A with paths (not full URLs), set the base:
# VITE_GCS_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://storage.googleapis.com/videos-bucket-123

# Why not “just call the Google JSON API” from the app?
# storage.objects.list needs OAuth or a service account. Putting a service
# account key in VITE_* would expose it to everyone — use Cloud Run / Functions
# if you need private buckets.

# ── Safari / iPhone (videos black or stuck) ───────────────────────────────────
# 1) Bucket CORS must allow your *page* origin (laptop AND phone dev URL), e.g.
#    http://192.168.x.x:5173 — include GET, HEAD, and Range-related response
#    headers. Example cors.json:
#    [{"origin":["http://localhost:5173","http://YOUR_LAN_IP:5173"],"method":["GET","HEAD"],"responseHeader":["Content-Type","Content-Length","Content-Range","Accept-Ranges","Range"],"maxAgeSeconds":3600}]
# 2) If videos still fail on Safari only, set (requires matching CORS):
#    VITE_VIDEO_CROSS_ORIGIN=anonymous
